# ENTERPRISE DEVELOPMENT RULES — ALTAHANY SAAS PLATFORM

## 1. CORE PHILOSOPHY

This project is a FULL Enterprise SaaS Platform for Wedding Services (Altahany).

The system is NOT a demo or template.
It MUST behave like a real production-grade SaaS used by a real company.

Everything generated must be:

* Production-ready
* Fully functional
* Database-connected
* API-driven
* Scalable
* Secure
* Maintainable

NO mockups. NO fake buttons. NO static pages without logic.

---

## 2. UI / UX PRINCIPLES

* Design must be PREMIUM, MODERN, and LUXURY
* Inspired by Apple-level simplicity + enterprise dashboards
* Mobile-first responsive design is mandatory
* Arabic RTL is default, English toggle supported
* Use Tailwind CSS only
* Use lucide-react for all icons (NO external icon libraries)
* Use soft elegant wedding branding (white, gold, soft pink tones)
* Smooth animations but performance-first
* Avoid clutter and heavy UI components
* Every page must feel like a real SaaS dashboard

---

## 3. CODE ARCHITECTURE RULES

* Use clean modular React components

* Use reusable hooks for logic

* Keep API logic separated from UI

* Use proper folder structure:
  /components
  /pages
  /hooks
  /services
  /utils
  /api

* All data MUST come from backend APIs

* No hardcoded values except UI defaults

* Use TypeScript strictly

---

## 4. BACKEND INTEGRATION RULES

* Every feature MUST be connected to real API
* All CRUD operations must persist in database
* Use proper REST API structure
* All forms must submit data to backend
* Validate all inputs on frontend + backend
* Handle API errors gracefully

---

## 5. ADMIN PANEL RULES (CRITICAL)

Admin dashboard MUST control EVERYTHING dynamically:

Admin can manage:

* Website content (text, images, sections)
* Services and packages
* Wedding halls directory
* Bookings and customers
* Invoices and quotations
* Email templates
* SEO settings
* Social media links
* Ads & banners
* AI tools settings
* Notifications system
* User roles and permissions

Any admin change MUST instantly reflect on frontend.

---

## 6. INVOICE & QUOTATION SYSTEM

Must be fully functional:

* PDF generation
* Print-ready layout
* Email sending
* WhatsApp sharing
* VAT support (UAE standards)
* QR code generation
* Logo, footer, watermark support
* Multi-language (Arabic/English)

No fake PDF or static templates allowed.

---

## 7. EMAIL SYSTEM

* Must support SMTP integration
* Must send real emails (no simulation)
* Admin must control SMTP settings
* Email templates must be editable
* Logs must be stored in database

---

## 8. MEDIA SYSTEM

* Upload images, videos, audio
* Optimize automatically (WebP preferred)
* Lazy loading required
* Drag & drop gallery management
* Watermark system supported
* CDN-ready structure

---

## 9. PERFORMANCE RULES

* Pages must load fast (<2s target)
* Optimize bundle size
* Avoid unnecessary rerenders
* Use lazy loading for heavy components
* SEO optimized structure required

---

## 10. SECURITY RULES

* JWT authentication required
* Role-based access control (RBAC)
* Input validation on all forms
* Protect APIs from unauthorized access
* Secure file uploads
* Rate limiting support

---

## 11. SEO REQUIREMENTS

* Meta tags on every page
* OpenGraph + Twitter cards
* Sitemap.xml
* Robots.txt
* Structured JSON-LD data
* SEO-friendly URLs

---

## 12. DEVELOPMENT BEHAVIOR

When building features:

* Always complete full workflow (UI + API + DB)
* Never leave feature half implemented
* Always connect frontend to backend
* Always ensure database persistence
* Always ensure admin control exists
* Always test logical flow of feature

---

## 13. TECH STACK RULES

* React + TypeScript only
* Tailwind CSS only for styling
* Node.js backend (Express or Hono)
* MySQL database
* No unnecessary libraries
* No UI frameworks like MUI, Ant, Bootstrap

---

## 14. FINAL SYSTEM GOAL

This platform must feel like:

* Enterprise SaaS platform
* Wedding industry CRM + ERP system
* Luxury premium product
* Real production system used by companies

NOT a template. NOT a demo.

---

## 15. NON-NEGOTIABLE RULE

If any feature is added:
You MUST ensure:

* It is fully functional
* It is connected to database
* It is accessible from admin panel
* It is integrated with frontend
* It is production safe